name: r-chk
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = "0.8.0" %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-chk
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/chk_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/chk/chk_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: fe24b081a7e35d5399412f55121b6b35b363b2023acb94fbdb08c55701d8ec81

build:
  merge_build_host: true  # [win]
  number: 0
  noarch: generic
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
    - cross-r-base {{ r_base }}    # [build_platform != target_platform]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-lifecycle
    - r-rlang
  run:
    - r-base
    - r-lifecycle
    - r-rlang

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('chk')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('chk')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://github.com/poissonconsulting/chk
  license: MIT
  summary: For developers to check user-supplied function arguments.  It is designed to be simple, fast and customizable.  Error messages follow the tidyverse style guide.
  license_family: MIT
  license_file:
    - {{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/MIT
    - LICENSE

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
